Method Detail

getSigar

public static org.hyperic.sigar.Sigar getSigar()
Retrieves an instance of SIGAR, which offers access to Operating System level information not typically available in the JDK. Important note: Not all SIGAR functions are implemented on all operating systems and architecture platforms. If you use SIGAR directly, make sure to test first on your target platform. For more information on SIGAR, please see: http://support.hyperic.com/display/SIGAR/Home

Returns:
the sigar instance.

getPidsWithQuery

public static List<Long> getPidsWithQuery(String query)
                                   throws org.hyperic.sigar.SigarException
Executes a SIGAR PTQL query, returning the PIDs of the processes that match the query. For more info on SIGAR's PTQL - Process Table Query Language, see: http://support.hyperic.com/display/SIGAR/PTQL

Parameters:
query - the PTQL query.
Returns:
the pids.
Throws:
org.hyperic.sigar.SigarException - in case of an error.

getPidsWithMainClass

public static List<Long> getPidsWithMainClass(String name)
                                       throws org.hyperic.sigar.SigarException
Returns the pids of Java processes where the name specified in in the process arguments. This will usually be the java process' main class, though that may not always be the case. PTQL Query: "State.Name.eq=java,Args.*.eq=" + name

Parameters:
name - the java main class or jar file name.
Returns:
the pids that match the query, may be zero, one or more.
Throws:
org.hyperic.sigar.SigarException - in case of an error.
